_faq_a_virtual_camera.translation: A "Camera Activity" is like a digital roll of film. It combines a camera filter you like from **Cameras** with a roll of film with a limited number of exposures (e.g. 12, 24, 36 exposures). Each camera you create groups your photos in a special album.

_faq_a_printing.translation: When you have filled all the exposures on a roll of film in a camera activity, or at any time, you can "send to print" the roll of film in the camera. This starts a countdown that allows your photos to be "developed" and visible after a period of time of your choice (e.g. 8, 24, 36 hours). When the time is up, your encrypted photos are decrypted and appear in your album.

_faq_q_store.translation: What can I do in Cameras?

_faq_a_store.translation: Cameras is where you can discover all the unique camera filters in the app. Each camera represents a filter with its own unique color, texture and character. By tapping on a camera, you can see "before and after" sample photos taken with that filter and choose the one that best suits your style.

_faq_q_new_activity.translation: How do I create a new activity?

_faq_a_new_activity.translation: Tap on a camera you like from Cameras to go to the "Select Camera Roll" screen. Here you can create your new camera activity by selecting one of the rolls of film with different exposure numbers (12, 24, 36, etc.) to use with the filter of your choice.

_faq_a_camera_cards.translation:
Each card represents a virtual camera and shows the following information:
- **Title:** The activity name, which you can change.
- Date and Location:** the date the activity was created and (if available) the location where the last photo was taken.
- Photo Info:** The number of exposures used on the roll of film you used (e.g. 15/24).

_faq_q_add_photo.translation: How do I add a photo to an existing activity?

_faq_a_add_photo.translation: If there is an empty exposure on the camera roll, you can tap on the corresponding camera activity on the "My Activities" screen to switch directly to the camera screen and continue taking pictures.

_faq_q_rename_camera.translation: How do I change the activity name?

_faq_a_rename_camera.translation: You can give your activity a custom name by tapping the pen icon next to each activity card.

_faq_q_send_to_print.translation: How do I send my photos to print?

_faq_a_send_to_print.translation: Tap the "Send to Print" button under the camera activity. Then choose how long you want your photos to be ready (e.g. 8, 12, 24, 36 hours). Remember, for shorter times (Express) you may need to watch a rewarded ad.

_faq_q_how_to_share.translation: How do I share an activity?

_faq_a_how_to_share.translation: On the "My Activities" screen, tap the share icon on the activity card you want to share. This will make the activity a shared activity and create an invitation link specific to the activity. You can send this link to your friends to invite them.

_faq_q_join_shared.translation: How do I join a shared activity?

_faq_a_join_shared.translation: Click on the invitation link sent to you. When the app opens, your request to join the activity will be sent to the activity owner. After the activity owner approves your request, the camera will appear on your "My Activities" screen and you can start taking photos.

_faq_a_requests_and_notifications.translation: The activity owner can view, approve or reject incoming requests by tapping the "Participants" icon on the activity card. You will receive a notification when you are approved or rejected. You can follow all your notifications from the bell icon in the upper right corner of the "My Activities" screen.

_faq_a_e2e_encryption.translation:
All your photos in shared activities are **end-to-end encrypted**. This means that **NOBODY** (including the Filmcam36 team) can see your photos except the activity owner and approved participants. A private "session key" is generated for each shared activity, only available on the participants' devices, and all encryption/decryption is done directly on your device. This keeps your memories completely private to you and your friends.
- If you accidentally delete the app while in a shared activity and the "session key" is lost, you will see a warning on the camera activity after you download the app again. For all shared camera activities where you see this warning, you can request a "session key" from the participants of that activity again.

_faq_a_album_tabs.translation: - **Albums:** Here you can find your camera developed photos from the activities you have created in albums.

_faq_q_photo_actions.translation: What can I do with my photos?

_faq_a_photo_actions.translation:
In full screen mode:
- **Save:** You can save the photo to your device's gallery.
- Share:** You can share the photo via other apps.
- Delete:** You can permanently delete the photo from the app.
- Make Profile Photo:** You can set the photo as your in-app profile picture.

_faq_a_ai_usage.translation: Go to the "AI" tab in the main navigation. Choose an AI effect you like and take your photo. After your photo is processed, it will appear in the "Album" -> "AI" tab.

_faq_q_edit_profile.translation: How do I edit my profile?

_faq_a_edit_profile.translation: When you are in the "Album" tab, you can update your profile information and photo in the profile section at the top or by going to "Account" in the Settings menu.

_faq_q_theme.translation: How do I change the app theme (Dark/Light Mode)?

_faq_a_theme.translation: You can select the desired theme from the Settings > "Dark/Light Mode" menu.

_faq_q_language.translation: How do I change the application language?

_faq_a_language.translation: You can change the application language in Settings > "Language".
